-- Treasury, Fed to meet on financial initiative
-- 
-- Mon Oct 13, 2008 11:28am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/13/us-financial-treasury-meeting-idUSTRE49C5CR20081013

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The U.S. Treasury and Federal Reserve are meeting on Monday with "leading financial market participants" to finalize details on a market stabilization initiative, a Treasury spokeswoman said. 

 The confirmation of the meeting comes as several European countries have announced initiatives to recapitalize banks and guarantee interbank lending. The Treasury and Fed could announce a similar initiative as early as Tuesday. The Wall Street Journal reported that U.S. Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson had called a meeting with top bank chiefs for 3 p.m.. (Reporting by  David Lawder ; Editing by Tom Hals)